snippet.textDisplay: Fun note: The song is "In the Wood Somewhere," in which a man awakes from a feverish sleep and is lured into the woods by a scream that sounds like his deceased beloved. He finds instead a helplessly wounded fox. He mercy kills it with a stone. He feels eyes upon him, perhaps those of the predator that wounded the fox. He flees. The last stanza of the song is a reflection: the man confesses that he abandoned his wish to reunite with his beloved in the afterlife because he discovered he feared death more.
